{"lemma":"أَحَبّ","slug":"أَحَبّ","root":"ح.ب.ب","root_slug":"ح-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَحَبّ","root":"حبب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6861"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love, to like","examples":[{"text":"أُحِبُّكَ","english":"I love you (to a male)"},{"text":"أُحِبُّكِ","english":"I love you (to a female)"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of حَبِيب (ḥabīb):; dearer; dearest, favourite","examples":[{"text":"وكانت الرابعة وهي ربيبة الوزير عبد الله تسكن في دارها. وهي أحبهن إليّ.","english":"My fourth wife, who was the daughter-in-law of the Wazir ‘Abdallah, used to live in her own house, and she was my favourite amongst them."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of حَبِيب (ḥabīb):; more agreeable; most agreeable"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of حَبِيب (ḥabīb, “dear”)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.ħab.ba/","/ʔa.ħabb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6861","headword_ar":"اَحَبُّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, loved, beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^aHab~u A_ilaY~a mino *aAka","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَحَبُّ اـِلَىَّ مِنْ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is more an object of love, affection, liking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approval,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is more lovely, charming, or pleasing, to me than that."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","tex